The paper deals with the computation of approximations in dynamic covering decision information systems, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of matrix-based approaches and algorithms for efficient computation suggests a focus on data management (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper involves experimentation and analysis of results, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
